The paper proposes a new framework for object segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The focus is on computer vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of top-down attention, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework involves the use of gating activities, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed network on benchmark datasets, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
